<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report on Beijing-Zhengzhou Railway Electrification Project </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Report on Beijing-Zhengzhou Railway Electrification Project </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1604034394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0245 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1604034394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shijiazhuang, April 16 (XINHUA) -- The upgrading 
work of the Beijing-Zhengzhou railway electrification project is 
now in its crucial stage. 
  Most of the earth work of the project has been completed and 
the first electric line has been laid on this section of the 
Beijing- Guangzhou railway. 
  The upgrading project of the electrification section, which 
is about 283 km long, started in March 1993. It is expected to 
open for traffic by the end of 1995. 
  It is one of the ten key projects of China's railway 
construction during the Eighth Five-Year Plan period 
(1991-1995). All the electric wiring and major parts for the 
project were imported and full use is being made of new- and 
high-technology. 

</TEXT>

