<H3> <TI>   Deng's Daughter Reports on Health of Deng Xiaoping </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deng's Daughter Reports on Health of Deng Xiaoping </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Says Deng `Very Healthy' </H4>

<F P=102> OW1504124494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1154 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1504124494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Zhu Youdi (2612 1635 2769) and Yang Zhaobo </F>
(2799 0340 3134)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 15 Apr (XINHUA) -- Responding to questions 
raised by reporters attending a news conference that the State 
Council Information Office held for Chinese and foreign 
reporters concerning "China's agenda for the 21st century," Deng 
Nan, vice minister in charge of the State Science and Technology 
Commission and Deng Xiaoping's daughter, said: "Deng Xiaoping 
is very healthy [shen ti hen jian kang 6500 7555 1771 0256 1660] 
and he is concerned with China's construction. He is also very 
much concerned with the implementation of all of `China's agenda 
for the 21st century.' My father still makes it a routine 
practice each day to finish work. He reads a lot, and he walks. 
We even played bridge the day before yesterday." 
  During the news conference, many overseas reporters asked 
about Deng Xiaoping's health. Answering a question raised by a 
Hong Kong reporter, Deng Nan said: "I understand your concern 
for my father's health. We are used to all kinds of talk about 
his health." 

</TEXT>

