<H3> <TI>   Papua New Guinea Governor General on Bilateral Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papua New Guinea Governor General on Bilateral Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1804165294 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1123 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1804165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Canberra, 8 Apr (XINHUA) -- According to a report 
from Port Moresby, Papua New Guinea Governor General Korowi 
indicated on 7 April: The Papua New Guinea Government attaches 
importance to developing economic and trade cooperation with 
China and hopes to import China's technology and personnel to 
help develop its medium and small enterprises. 
  Korowi made the above statement when receiving credentials 
from the newly appointed Chinese Ambassador to Papua New Guinea 
Yuan Zude. 
  During the conversation, Korowi highly commended China's 
accomplishments in its reform and opening up and its important 
roles in international affairs. He was satisfied that Papua New 
Guinea- Chinese relations have been progressing smoothly and 
that both countries have been mutually supporting, and actively 
cooperating with, each other on international issues. 
  He said: He expects China to expand its investments in Papua 
New Guinea and to develop Papua New Guinea's resources to 
enhance bilateral cooperation and economic and trade exchanges 
that are mutually beneficial. 

</TEXT>

