<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sino-DPRK Session on Border River Shipping Closes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sino-DPRK Session on Border River Shipping Closes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004030994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0253 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2004030994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Changchun, April 20 (XINHUA) -- The 33rd session of 
the Sino-DPRK (Democratic People's Republic of Korea) joint 
committee for shipping on their border rivers closed here 
Tuesday [20 April]. 
  During the 10-day meeting the committee discussed last 
year's 
work and the plan for 1994 put forward by the two sides. 
  In a friendly atmosphere the two sides reached agreement on 
issues of navigation safety, surveys and dredging. 
  An accord of the 33rd session of the joint committee was 
also 
passed during the 10-day meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

