<F P=103> OW1904160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala lumpur, April 19 (XINHUA) -- Malaysian 
defense minister Najib Tun Razak today met visiting Chinese 
General Zhang Wannian, chief of the General Staff of the Chinese 
People's Liberation Army. 
  The Chinese general is here to attend the Defense Services 
Asia '94 exhibition. 
  During their meeting, Najib and Zhang agreed that reciprocal 
visits of the leaders of the two countries should continue in 
the interest of mutual understanding and friendship. 
  Malaysia sees China as a close neighbor, said Najib. Prime 
Minister Mahathir Mohamed's visit to China last year further 
strengthened the bilateral relationship, he added. 
  A growing number of Malaysians are visiting China, and they 
are getting excited about China's economic prospects, Najib said. 
  When introducing China's defense policy to Najib, Zhang said 
China will not seek hegemony, commit aggression, align with any 
other country or build military bases abroad, adding the Chinese 
Army is totally committed to defense. 

</TEXT>

