<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Maputo, April 15 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese Red Cross 
Committee today granted 20,000 U.S. dollars to the Mozambican 
National Committee of disaster prevention and resistance. 
  Chinese Ambassador to Mozambique Mi Shiheng, on behalf of 
the 
Chinese Red Cross, handed over the cheque to deputy director of 
the Mozambican committee Oldemiro Baloe. 
  Mi said at the hand-over ceremony that the grant is a 
response to Mozambique's appeal for emergent aid for Nampula 
Province, northern Mozambique, where people have suffered great 
losses from tornado and storms. 
  Meanwhile, Baloi expressed thanks for the Chinese grant. 

