<H3> <TI>   China, Mozambique Sign Protocol on Medical Assistance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    China, Mozambique Sign Protocol on Medical Assistance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1504194694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1933 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1504194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Maputo, April 15 (XINHUA) -- China and Mozambique 
agreed here today that China will continue sending medical teams 
to Mozambique. 
  A protocal on this issue was signed by Chinese Ambassador to 
Mozambique Mi Shiheng and Mozambican Deputy Health Minister 
Maria Campos on behalf of their respective government. 
  Campos said after the signing ceremony that China has been 
sending medical teams to Mozambique since the Southern African 
country declared independence in 1975. 
  The Chinese medical teams have played an active role in the 
development of the Mozambican health sector, he said. 
  There are now eight Chinese medical teams in Mozambique. 
Under the new protocal, a ninth 11-member medical team will 
arrive in Mozambique this year. 

