<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Petroleum Venture To Involve Thailand, SRV, PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Petroleum Venture To Involve Thailand, SRV, PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2104055494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0525 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2104055494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bangkok, April 21 (XINHUA) -- The Petroleum 
Authority of Thailand (PTT) will undertake joint ventures with 
the Charoen Pokphand Group and petrochemical firms in China and 
Vietnam. 
  The joint ventures involve a total investment of 6,420 
million baht (256.8 million U.S. dollars). Of the amount, 635 
million baht (25.4 million U.S. dollars) is invested by the PTT. 
The joint ventures will operate petroleum business in China, 
Vietnam and Thailand, according to official bulletin available 
here today. 
  The business is in line with the policy and directions for 
state enterprises to move towards the international trade and 
strengthen relations between Thailand and China and Vietnam. 
  It said the cabinet has given the green light to the plan. 
  The joint venture in China involves the setting up of oil 
stations with China's Guangdong, Shanghai, Tianjin and Talian 
petrochemical firms, the bulletin. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
